<DocsLayout 
    title="rugbyclaw scores" 
    description="Show today's matches across your favorite leagues">
    
    <p class="lead">Show today's matches across your favorite leagues</p>

    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <pre><code>rugbyclaw scores [options]</code></pre>

    <h2>Options</h2>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Option</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Default</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td><code>--json</code></td>
                <td>Output as JSON</td>
                <td>false</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><code>--quiet</code></td>
                <td>Minimal output</td>
                <td>false</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Examples</h2>
    
    <h3>View today's matches</h3>
    <pre><code>rugbyclaw scores</code></pre>
    
    <p><strong>Output:</strong></p>
    <pre><code>üèâ Rugby Scores - Sunday, Feb 2, 2026

Top 14
  Toulouse vs Racing 92          15:00
  Lyon vs Bordeaux              17:00

Premiership  
  Saracens vs Leicester         14:30
  Bath vs Harlequins            16:45</code></pre>

    <h3>JSON output</h3>
    <pre><code>rugbyclaw scores --json</code></pre>
    <p>Returns structured JSON for scripts/automation.</p>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Shows matches happening today</li>
        <li>Only displays leagues you selected in config</li>
        <li>Times shown in your configured timezone</li>
        <li>Updates when you run the command (not live-updating)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tips</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Run this command in the morning to see today's schedule</li>
        <li>Combine with <code>watch</code> for live updates: <code>watch -n 60 rugbyclaw scores</code></li>
        <li>Use <code>--json</code> for integration with other tools</li>
    </ul>

